<paragraph blockId="8.[151,552,1257,1283]" box="[151,552,1257,1283]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,552,1257,1283]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,552,1257,1283]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[207,375,1257,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admiranda">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,375,1257,1283]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">N. admiranda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1327,1568]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1327,1352]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The coloration and the pattern are similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="van Eecke" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[962,1118,1329,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis box="[962,1118,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">N. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. In the male genitalia, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[303,459,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admiranda">
<emphasis box="[303,459,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">N. admiranda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group differs from other species-groups in the combination of such features as the broad, almost elliptical valve, the presence of the ventral-apical costal process, the thin, spike-shaped distalventral costal process, the ventral costal plate directed at a small angle to the costa, the very large ampulla, the absence of a subapical saccular process, and the extremely long and broad medial diverticulum of vesica armed with spines apically. In the female genitalia, the fascia-shaped, inflated postvaginal plate and the reduction of the appendix bursae are unique within the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
